    {
      "id": "role-initial-types",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Primitive Families",
      "position": {
        "x": 466,
        "y": 475
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Primitive Families\n\nThe modern Twilite model is organized around a light shared substrate plus composed roles.\n\nCore primitive families include:\n- `declaration`\n- content-bearing nodes such as `markdown`\n- boundary primitives such as `port` and `portal`\n- authority primitives such as `bridge`\n- dedicated view primitives such as `icon-view`, `port-view`, `document-view`, and `editor-view`\n\nAnything more specialized can still be graph-local or class-backed.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
